title: What to watch: Your weekend TV schedule
text:
FOXSPORTS What to watch: Your weekend TV schedule Formula One, MotoGP, NASCAR and Formula E are all racing this weekend. Be sure not to miss a second of the action with our weekend TV schedule: 
Lewis Hamilton will look to secure his third Formula One World Championship at the United States Grand Prix at the Circuit of the Americas in Austin, Texas this weekend. Andrew Ferraro / LAT Photographic Oct 23, 2015 at 9:26a ET 0Shares 
Formula One heads to Texas for the United States Grand Prix this weekend while MotoGP heads to Sepang for its penultimate round of the season. NASCAR is at Talladega with the Cup and the Truck series while the second season of Formula E kicks off in Beijing. 
Full weekend TV schedule (all times ET and subject to change) 
Friday, Oct. 23: 
11 a.m. - Formula One FP1 - Texas - NBCSN/ GP RaceCast 1 p.m. - NASCAR Truck practice - Talladega - FS1/ RaceTrax 2 p.m. - FIA WEC highlights - Fuji - FS1 2 p.m. - NASCAR Cup practice - Talladega - NBCSN/ RaceTrax 3 p.m. - NASCAR Truck practice - Talladega - FS1/ RaceTrax 3 p.m. - Formula One FP2 - Texas - NBCSN/ GP RaceCast 4:30 p.m. - NASCAR Cup practice - Talladega - NBCSN/ RaceTrax 
Saturday, Oct. 24: 
3:30 a.m. - FIA Formula E - Beijing - FS1 10:30 a.m. - NASCAR Truck qualifying - Talladega - FS1/ RaceTrax 12:30 p.m. - Formula One FP3 - Texas - NBCSN (delayed) 1 p.m. - NASCAR Truck racing - Talladega - FOX/ RaceTrax 2 p.m. - Formula One qualifying - Texas - NBCSN/ GP RaceCast 4 p.m. - NASCAR Cup qualifying - Talladega - NBCSN/ RaceTrax 
Sunday, Oct. 25: 
2:30 a.m. - MotoGP racing - Malaysia - FS1 10 a.m. - NASCAR Raceday - Talladega - FS1 1 p.m. - Moto3 - Malaysia - FS2 2 p.m. - Moto2 - Malaysia - FS2 2:30 p.m. - Formula One racing - Texas - NBC/ GP RaceCast 2:30 p.m. - NASCAR Cup racing - Talladega - NBCSN/ RaceTrax 8 p.m. - NASCAR Victory Lane - Talladega - FS1 (delayed) 0
